    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="bpl.00016.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden<ptr target="bpl.00016_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1887-07-05">July 5 '87</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>I shall get a good 4 or 5 room shanty by the water or in the woods<ptr
                target="n4116"/></p>
            
            <p>Yes I sent <hi rend="underline">you</hi> the card I ought to have sent to Baxter<ptr
                target="n6000"/>&#8212;Can you send it to him<ptr
                    target="bpl.00016_n2"/>&#8212;this one
                also?&#8212;To day, Tuesday, we have the great relief of a cloudy, showery, fairly
                coolish day &#38; I feel better&#8212;previously we had had a week of great heat
                &#38; glaring sun &#38; it had sapped me pretty well down&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001rv" facs="bpl.00016.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
